body:
The schema validation fails for below

```
{
	"$schema": "http://json-schema.org/draft-07/schema#",
	"type": "object",
	"$id": "http://example.com/root.json",
	"properties": {
		"Persons": {
			"type": "array",
			"$id": "#/properties/Persons",
			"items": {
				"$id": "#/properties/Persons/items",
				"type": "object",
				"properties": {
					"Name": {
						"type": "string"
					},
					"Contact": {
						"type": "array",
						"items": {
							"type": "object",
							"properties": {
								"Email": {
									"type": "string"
								}
							}

						}
					}

				}
			}
		}
	}
}
```

## Actual behavior when validated against below json    
```
{
"Persons":[
      {
        "Name":"ABC",
        "Contact":[
            {
              "Email":"something@something.com"
            }
        ]

      }

    ]
}


```

ERROR: The JSON is not valid with the schema.Exception :Type : System.ExceptionMessage : The JSON is not valid with the schema.HResult : -2146233088CategoryInfo : InvalidData: (:) [Test-Json], ExceptionFullyQualifiedErrorId : InvalidJsonAgainstSchema,Microsoft.PowerShell.Commands.TestJsonCommandErrorDetails : ArrayItemNotValid: #/Persons[0]{ArrayExpected: #/Persons[0].Contact}InvocationInfo :MyCommand : Test-JsonScriptLineNumber :
